# Dooers Agent Starter — rules for AI assistants

## Architecture (mandatory)

- **Handler** lives in `src/modules/agent/agent.py` — async generator with `yield send.*`
- **Workflow** in `workflow.py` — OpenAI Agents SDK `Runner.run`, not raw LLM calls
- **Capabilities** in `src/modules/agent/capabilities/` — one domain per file, register handoffs in `workflow.py`
- **Settings UI** in `schemas.py` — use `SettingsField`, `SettingsFieldVisibility.CREATOR`
- **HTTP routes** only in `main.py` — do not add business logic there

## SDK contract

- Package: `dooers-agents-server` (`import dooers`)
- Every turn: `yield send.run_start()` … `yield send.run_end()`
- Persist threads via SDK — never write SQL for messages/events
- Read `docs/02-sdk-contract.md` before changing handler signatures

## Do NOT

- Commit secrets (`.env`, API keys, service account JSON)
- Reimplement WebSocket protocol or WhatsApp HMAC — use SDK helpers
- Reference or import private Dooers codebases — use only this starter and public packages (`dooers-agents-server`, `dooers-agents-client`, `dooers-cli`)

## When adding features

| Feature | Files to touch |
|---------|----------------|
| New domain | `capabilities/<name>.py`, `workflow.py` |
| Studio field | `schemas.py` |
| RAG field | `schemas.py`, optional allowlist in capability |
| Form | tool in capability + form builders in `agent.py` |
| External channel | `dispatch()` or `channels/` |

## Code style

- Python 3.11+, ruff line-length 120
- Match existing naming: `create_<capability>`, `dooers_agent_handler`
- Run `uv run poe check` after edits

## Deploy

Read `docs/08-deploy.md` before suggesting deploy. The creator runs `dooers login` and `dooers push` — do not commit secrets or run push without their credentials.

Recipe: `docs/recipes/deploy-with-dooers-push.md`

